    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-10-16T14:01:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-10-16T14:01:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330.13/10–654: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d264fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MEYERSH1"
                            >Meyers</persName> of <gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>. Repeated for
                        information to New York as telegram <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss>
                        48 and to London as telegram 2181.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-10-16T14:01:00-05:00"
                            >October 16, 1954—2:01 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1418. Re disarmament (<gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss> 32, rptd Paris
                    1299, London 2000, Oct 7; <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss>s [<gloss
                        target="#t_Delga1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Delgas</hi>
                    </gloss>] 63 and 64, rptd Paris 1295, London 1996, Oct 7)<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d264fn2">None printed. (330.13/10–654)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Request Embassy urgently see appropriate high-ranking official French
                        Government conveying following: <list>
                            <label>a)</label>
                            <item>Dept seriously concerned by extent <persName corresp="#p_MOCHJ1"
                                    >Jules Moch</persName>’s free-wheeling tactics on disarmament
                                item at <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. While <gloss
                                    target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>, US, Canadian delegations acting in
                                concert, now appears <persName corresp="#p_MOCHJ1">Moch</persName>
                                has been seeing <persName corresp="#p_VYSHINSKYAY1"
                                    >Vyshinsky</persName> without informing other Dels. <gloss
                                    target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> had wondered why <persName
                                    corresp="#p_VYSHINSKYAY1">Vyshinsky</persName> appeared aware
                                many matters discussed at meetings four Western delegations. Oct 14
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MOCHJ1">Moch</persName> inadvertently
                                disclosed he had been shown USSR amendments to Western-supported
                                disarmament resolution prior to Canada, which had introduced this
                                resolution. <persName corresp="#p_MOCHJ1">Moch</persName> has
                                consistently sought accept Soviet amendments to Western resolution,
                                mostly without revision, and threatened speak in their support
                                despite US, <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>, Canadian attitude,
                                with consequent damaging effect on substantive positions previously
                                held by four Western allies. While US, <gloss target="#t_UK1"
                                    >UK</gloss>, Canadian, French dels. previously agreed USSR
                                should be invited cosponsor Canadian resolution only on assurance no
                                amendments would be accepted, <persName corresp="#p_MOCHJ1"
                                    >Moch</persName> now declares not aware this
                                understanding.</item>
                            <label>b)</label>
                            <item>Above facts make Dept view apprehensively future disarmament
                                discussions, since <persName corresp="#p_MOCHJ1">Moch</persName>’s
                                attitude indicates may be divergences between Western allies caused
                                not by merits disarmament issues but by other factors.</item>
                            <label>c)</label>
                            <item>USG deeply desires explore whether new Soviet proposal involves
                                advance toward agreement or is only clever propaganda gambit. This
                                requires careful, extended discussions. It also needs closest
                                cooperation Western participants these discussions. Such cooperation
                                seems strained now by <persName corresp="#p_MOCHJ1"
                                >Moch</persName>’s attitude and may become worse if he continues on
                                present course. Dept. would hope French Govt could advise French
                                    <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> Del concert and cooperate with
                                    <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>, Canadian, US Delegations on
                                disarmament item.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>. We do not know whether <persName
                            corresp="#p_MOCHJ1">Moch</persName> acting for self or on instructions
                        and this might be good opportunity probe this important question.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HOOVERHJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
